What exactly has she done for people, women, men or whoever? I'm really confused as to why she is 'woman of the decade'? It can't be because she's been a successful woman - she's far from the first, Music is littered with legendary women with incredible careers inn their respective fields, markets over many decades - Diana Ross, Tina Turner, Madonna, Cher, Kylie Minogue, Celine Dion, Mariah Carey, Barbra Streisand, Adele - the list goes on and on. So has she been a champion of women's issues (whatever they are in what is the most Egalitarian western world there has ever been)? Is she in Africa saving women from mutilation or abuse? Is she in Russia, saving women from abuse? is she in the Islamic world, saving women from extreme oppression, enforced marriage, honour killings? No - she's a vacuous pop singer singing with infantile lyrics, who has somehow managed to paint herself as some sort of victim - in fact, that's it - she's furthered the cause of female victimhood! The newest way Westerners occupy their time because basically, things have never been so good. Next...

There'll be many successful women in that audience, who have done it by themselves, no doubt angry that Taylor once again repeats the stereotype that any successful woman in Music has been abused, raped, oppressed, taken advantage of...
